Pour the @water{300%milliliter} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, then bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave the rice to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the
rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice is cooking, drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Next, put a #large saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Stir in the @Chipotle Paste{20%grams}, @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, black beans,
@Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @water{200%milliliter} for the sauce.

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Once combined, stir in the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams}. IMPORTANT:
Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Bring the stew to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked
through and the sauce has thickened, ~{13-15%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the stew has finished simmering, mix the @Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{25%grams} and
@Butter{20%grams} into the pan until combined and melted.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a
splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the chilli chicken one pot.

Scatter over the cheese to finish. Enjoy!